Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.40,0:00:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A world... Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A world for you who seek freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.84,0:00:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stretches out right before your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.01,0:00:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If your endless dreams are your guide,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.01,0:00:25.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,surpass them, under the flag of your beliefs!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.19,0:00:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Making a splash,\NI've just started on my search
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.69,0:00:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heading towards a world without end
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.20,0:00:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart bursting with enthusiasm,\NI'll go to the ends of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.37,0:00:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In search of light yet unseen
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.71,0:01:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the summer sun\Nsways the sails of my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.82,0:01:13.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the cue to open the door to a new world
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.33,0:01:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sailing through the rocky waves of despair
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.34,0:01:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We head beyond the horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.01,0:01:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Making a splash,\NI've just started on my search
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.68,0:01:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heading towards a world without end
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.19,0:01:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart bursting with enthusiasm,\NI'll go to the ends of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.36,0:01:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In search of light yet unseen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.51,0:02:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take those two and beat it already
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.11,0:02:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while you're still alive, you small fries!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.12,0:02:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sky island exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.12,0:02:14.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.13,0:02:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.13,0:02:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The new era they're talking about is crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.13,0:02:28.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The era where pirates have dreams\Nwill be over, they say?! Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.51,0:02:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People's dreams... have no end!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.19,0:02:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Legendary Family! 'Noland the Liar'"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.19,0:02:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously... Seriously... Seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.20,0:02:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously... that darn orangutan!\NHe wrecked the ship even more!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.20,0:03:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This ship has really started to fall apart.\NMaybe it's about time to replace it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.14,0:03:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare start saying\Ninconsiderate things, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.84,0:03:07.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you dare!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.18,0:03:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know exactly how we got this ship, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.18,0:03:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.18,0:03:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, Usopp.\NComplaining won't get us anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.52,0:03:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Going Merry is an important part of the team.\N--You know exactly...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.79,0:03:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--You...! You...!\N--So let's work hard and repair the ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.53,0:03:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--How we... How... How... How we...!\N--Luffy... You're such a...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.70,0:03:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.20,0:03:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!! Are you repairing\Nthe ship or wrecking it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.54,0:03:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm really trying to fix it, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.87,0:03:37.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops, it got broke again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.21,0:03:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.28,0:03:44.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We left Mock Town and headed east\Nby circling around the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.25,0:03:46.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost here on the map.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.25,0:03:48.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man... what's his name again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.92,0:03:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Montblanc Cricket.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.26,0:03:54.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that man who talks of\Ndreams lives there, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.93,0:03:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Amazing!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.93,0:04:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's his house?! That's a palace!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.20,0:04:06.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this Montblanc Cricket guy mega-rich?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.20,0:04:07.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiots! Look closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.87,0:04:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dreamer, huh? He does seem to be vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.25,0:04:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.58,0:04:21.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?! It's just a board?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.59,0:04:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.25,0:04:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The actual house is only half of it.\NThe rest is just a veneer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.59,0:04:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He seems like a very cheap guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.59,0:04:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of dreams did he talk about\Nthat would get him driven out?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.60,0:04:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the details,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.27,0:04:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I heard that he said a huge\Namount of gold rests in Jaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.94,0:04:40.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.94,0:04:43.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that some pirate's buried\Ntreasure or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.61,0:04:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.98,0:04:48.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.31,0:04:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dig the ground, Chopper! Gold will appear!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.65,0:04:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will if I dig?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.32,0:04:54.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Living alone in such a remote area?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.65,0:04:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello. I'm coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.32,0:04:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't you wait a moment?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.66,0:05:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? No one's here. Hello!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.59,0:05:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No answer...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.60,0:05:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot, wait! What're you\Ngonna do if this guy's dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.60,0:05:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, everyone! No one's home!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.27,0:05:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.61,0:05:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...a picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.27,0:05:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is quite an old book.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.61,0:05:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? It's titled "Noland the Liar."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.65,0:05:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, that's a cool title! Nice idea for a book!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.65,0:05:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Noland the Liar"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.32,0:05:31.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know it, Sanji-kun? But it says\Nit was published in the North Blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.32,0:05:34.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I was born in the North Blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.33,0:05:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't I told you guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.33,0:05:39.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's news. I thought you\Nwere from the East, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.50,0:05:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I grew up there.\N--Quiet, Chopper! What're you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.67,0:05:44.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.87,0:05:54.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Noland the Liar"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.67,0:05:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a famous story in the North.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.67,0:05:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a fairy tale, but I've heard that this\NNoland guy actually existed long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.71,0:05:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a story from long, long ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.72,0:06:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A story that took place 400 long years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.32,0:06:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man named Montblanc Noland\Nlived in a North Blue country.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.66,0:06:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland, an explorer, always talked\Nabout his incredible adventures.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.33,0:06:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the villagers couldn't tell\Nif those stories were true or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.01,0:06:27.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, he reported to the King\Nafter coming back from his travels.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.05,0:06:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I saw a mountain of gold\Non an island in the great sea."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.38,0:06:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The courageous king set sail to the\Ngreat sea to see if the story was true,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.06,0:06:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,taking 2,000 soldiers along with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.39,0:06:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After surviving great storms\Nand battling against monsters,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.40,0:06:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only the King, Noland and 100\Nsoldiers made it to the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.74,0:06:58.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, what they found\Nthere was just a jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.41,0:07:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, he was sentenced\Nto death for the crime of lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.05,0:07:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland's last words were as follows:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.72,0:07:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"That's right! The mountain\Nof gold sank in the sea!"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.72,0:07:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The King and the others were dumbfounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.73,0:07:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one believed Noland any longer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.73,0:07:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because Noland continued\Nto lie until his very death.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.73,0:07:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This book is based on the North Blue\Nfairy tale "Noland the Liar."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.74,0:07:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Montblanc Cricket is a descendant\Nof that Montblanc Noland?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.78,0:07:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that fairy tale a lot when I was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.45,0:07:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There isn't anyone in the North Blue\Nwho doesn't know the tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.12,0:07:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're all from the North Blue,\Nso we often got told
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.46,0:07:48.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that if we lied a lot, we'd be\Nsentenced to death like Noland.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.80,0:07:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is getting more and more interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.46,0:07:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never would've imagined that\NJaya was the island in that fairy tale.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.80,0:07:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, after 400 years,\Na descendant of Noland the Liar
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.80,0:08:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is looking for the gold on this island, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.41,0:08:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to clear the name of his ancestor,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.41,0:08:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who was called a big liar\Nand laughed at until he died...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.12,0:08:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This family cracks me up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.12,0:08:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does he really think that\Nhe can clear the name
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.69,0:08:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of his 400 year-old ancestor by\Nbringing back a few pieces of gold?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.46,0:08:30.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds like he's weak in the head!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.81,0:08:42.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alas, the liar died...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.18,0:08:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...before he could even become\Na brave warrior on the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.85,0:08:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look at me! And don't add in a\Nheartbreaking sentence on your own!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.53,0:08:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy fell into the sea!!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.19,0:08:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.53,0:09:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.47,0:09:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got guts, relaxing at someone's\Nhouse without permission!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.80,0:09:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sea in this area is my turf!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.14,0:09:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hey, Usopp! Go grab Luffy!\N--Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.77,0:09:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're after the gold, aren't you? Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.18,0:09:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Sanji!!\N--Sanji-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.52,0:09:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. It didn't hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.19,0:09:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.43,0:09:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot... You shouldn't\Nunderestimate your opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.20,0:09:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Move! I'll handle this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.54,0:09:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what were you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.71,0:09:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw... bubbles coming out of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.58,0:09:51.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I was looking in the water,\Nthen suddenly a chestnut appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.58,0:09:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The chestnut was actually a guy,\Nand he dragged me into the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.45,0:09:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.59,0:10:05.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring more cold towels! Open up the windows!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.60,0:10:08.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Caisson disease?\N--Is this guy sick?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.60,0:10:12.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's a sickness that divers sometimes get.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.27,0:10:15.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it doesn't usually become\Na longstanding condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.94,0:10:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to a lack of decompression\Nwhen surfacing from the seabed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.94,0:10:23.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the nitrogen dissolved in the\Nblood gets released quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.65,0:10:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and forms gas bubbles at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.65,0:10:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since the gas bubbles expand\Ninside and outside of blood vessels,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.65,0:10:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they cause problems to\Nblood flow, muscle and joints.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.32,0:10:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's some bizarre phenomenon, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.33,0:10:39.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably kept diving\Nevery day without giving time
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.86,0:10:43.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for those bubbles to disappear from the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.67,0:10:45.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.67,0:10:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, but he's taking a risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.01,0:10:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In some cases, caisson disease can...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.34,0:10:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...cause death.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.32,0:11:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh hey, it's you, Masira. So you're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.66,0:11:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alive? What're you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.33,0:11:14.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind. In any case,\Nwhat was that gunfire about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.67,0:11:17.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly, brother! Do you think\Nsomething happened to the old-timer?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.67,0:11:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry! I'm getting all worked up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.34,0:11:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old-timer! Are you all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.68,0:11:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've come to kill us!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.68,0:11:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you guys doing here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.05,0:11:33.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do to the old-timer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.05,0:11:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? We're looking after this guy\Nright now, so go somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.72,0:11:40.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! They aren't really gonna hear us out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.73,0:11:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--They're savages, you know!\N--You know!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.73,0:11:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Everyone, evacuate through the windows!\N--You...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.26,0:11:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...guys are so nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.40,0:11:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're listening!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.05,0:12:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys live here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.72,0:12:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the old-timer's house is the\Nheadquarters of the Saruyama Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.72,0:12:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we sleep on our ships most of the time
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.73,0:12:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because this house is too small for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.40,0:12:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you guys are too big.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.73,0:12:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, to those Giant guys you\Nlook like a ball of earwax, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.74,0:12:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are they getting along so well?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.07,0:12:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can probably relate to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.44,0:12:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's amazing that you guys\Nkicked him off when you're so small!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.11,0:12:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Really? You can do it, too.\N--Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.78,0:12:42.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you can because you're a monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.12,0:12:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy, he's come around!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.12,0:12:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's awake?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.79,0:12:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, he's right, I can kick Masira...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.13,0:12:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey old diamond-head!\NI wanna ask you something!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.74,0:13:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I caused you trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.41,0:13:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were just\Nmore idiots after the gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.08,0:13:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! You have gold bullion?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.08,0:13:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go after it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.41,0:13:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it that you wanna ask me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.78,0:13:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old guy, we wanna go to the sky island!\NPlease tell us how to get there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.12,0:13:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sky island?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.79,0:13:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys believe in the sky island?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.13,0:13:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop it! He's a sick person!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.47,0:13:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no sky island, old guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.14,0:13:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.14,0:13:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know someone who said there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.48,0:13:43.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But people call him a legendary big liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.18,0:13:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His family became a laughing stock forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.85,0:13:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.19,0:13:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's an old story that\Nmost North Blue people know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.86,0:13:56.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Noland the Liar" is the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.53,0:13:59.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, it's not me!\NHe's got a different name, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.86,0:14:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Noland's name is,\Nif I'm not mistaken, Montblanc Noland.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.47,0:14:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that you're Noland's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.80,0:14:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A descendant?! Could this place\Nbe the island in that story?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.81,0:14:15.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph! He's my granddad's\Ngranddad's granddad's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.15,0:14:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's my distant ancestor... What a nuisance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.18,0:14:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt there's a drop\Nof his blood in my body...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.19,0:14:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although the Montblanc family\Nwas driven out of the country then,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.66,0:14:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and has kept a low profile,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.43,0:14:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,people continue to\Ndenounce our family to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.86,0:14:36.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But no one in the family hates him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.20,0:14:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.54,0:14:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because Noland was an\Nextraordinarily honest person.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.87,0:14:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in that picture book...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.21,0:14:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland's last excuse in\Nthe picture book is like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.05,0:14:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"That's right! The mountain\Nof gold sank in the sea!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.25,0:14:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A stupid-looking face is drawn in this book...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.92,0:15:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but he shed many tears\Nand died a regrettable death.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.19,0:15:04.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was sure that the island\Nhe reached was Jaya,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.46,0:15:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where he found the wreckage of a city of gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.53,0:15:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He felt that there was no way\Nit was just an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.20,0:15:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland insisted that the ruins had\Nsubmerged due to crustal movements,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.21,0:15:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but everyone thought he was\Nmaking excuses out of desperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.88,0:15:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland was executed in front\Nof the laughing onlookers,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.92,0:15:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and only the name "Liar" remained.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.59,0:15:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see! You're looking for\Nthe city of gold on the seabed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.59,0:15:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to clear the Montblanc family's name!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.92,0:15:35.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.93,0:15:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Usopp!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.26,0:15:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd die...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.26,0:15:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How honest my distant ancestor was,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.27,0:15:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or how great an explorer he was,\Nhas nothing to do with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.27,0:15:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you understand how a kid would\Nfeel being laughed at by strangers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.88,0:15:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just because he's the\Ndescendant of such an idiot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.28,0:15:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how I grew up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.32,0:16:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... yeah, over the past 400 years,\Nmany set sail to restore our family's honor,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.26,0:16:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,though all of them went missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.26,0:16:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was ashamed of such a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.93,0:16:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran away from home and became a pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.93,0:16:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? You're a pirate, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.60,0:16:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that I wanted to become a pirate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.27,0:16:25.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to escape from Noland's spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.28,0:16:29.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And over time, I came to\Nhave my own pirate group.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.95,0:16:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At long last, I entered the Grand Line,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.32,0:16:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I spent all my time on adventures.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.32,0:16:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But ten years ago, my ship\Nreached this island by accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.66,0:16:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Strangely enough, only I,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.86,0:16:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who continued to hate the Montblanc\Nfamily and Noland the most, made it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.33,0:16:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The island didn't have a city of gold,\Njust like the picture book said.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.74,0:16:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I stood on a cape of the island,\NI felt that it was destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.68,0:17:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no place to escape to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.34,0:17:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's settle this, Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.95,0:17:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell, no! Captain, we're not gonna have\Nanything to do with your family's problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.99,0:17:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you insist on searching\Nfor the gold, do it alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.66,0:17:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're splitting here. Goodbye, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.66,0:17:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's there, that's fine.\NIf it's not there, that's fine, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.00,0:17:29.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not that I want to prove his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.34,0:17:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a duel with the man\Nwho threw a wrench into my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.68,0:17:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to set the record straight before I die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.06,0:17:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is indeed a man's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.06,0:17:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what about them?\NWhy are those monkeys, here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.40,0:17:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There must've been an exciting drama
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.27,0:17:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,spoken with the fists of men\Ncommitted to exploring the seabed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.24,0:18:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those guys are fans of the picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.34,0:18:02.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fans?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.67,0:18:05.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a quite simple connection.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.01,0:18:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was five or six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.01,0:18:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They heard a rumor about\Nme and barged in on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.01,0:18:16.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They said, "We think\NNoland's gold definitely exists!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.05,0:18:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shojo!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.06,0:18:20.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ready to take me on\Nafter suddenly kicking me like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.39,0:18:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's an outrageous\Nfalse accusation, Masira!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.39,0:18:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make me angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.06,0:18:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sea around here is deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.07,0:18:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the dark, cold sea, you're\Nhaunted by a deeper solitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.07,0:18:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just dived and searched alone every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.74,0:18:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They just came into my life
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.91,0:18:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and became my underlings without\Nmy permission, and they romp around.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.12,0:18:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Single-minded idiots like them...\Nmake me feel relieved, to be honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.79,0:18:55.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.13,0:19:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do. Yeah, real comrades give\Neach other strength and...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.73,0:19:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, putting the story\Nabout those monkeys aside...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.40,0:19:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, don't ask! Clench your teeth!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.41,0:19:12.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said... I wanna go\Nto the sky island, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.75,0:19:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a hasty one!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.41,0:19:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I did tell you, right? The witness\Nto the sky island is that Noland the Liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.79,0:19:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you have anything to do with him,\Nyou'll be laughed at like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.46,0:19:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! He's been to the sky island, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.13,0:19:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, this doesn't say he did, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.46,0:19:34.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A logbook?! Could it be Noland's?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.47,0:19:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.47,0:19:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Read around there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.47,0:19:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing... A logbook from 400 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.47,0:19:47.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sea Ephemeris Year 1120, June 21st, Sunny.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.48,0:19:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We left Villa, a cheerful town.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.48,0:19:55.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Following the Log Pose, we should be\Nheading east-northeast from the harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.52,0:19:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We got a rare item from a bumboat\Nthat we came across during the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.52,0:20:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a ski-like one-person boat called a waver.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.19,0:20:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a mysterious boat that can generate wind\Nand move even on a day without wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.53,0:20:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that you need to get the hang\Nof it to ride, and I couldn't manage it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.54,0:20:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, it's become\Na perfect toy for my crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.21,0:20:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way! What's this? I want it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.87,0:20:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that, keep reading!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.21,0:20:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power for this seems to be a\Nproduct found only on the sky island,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.21,0:20:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I hear that many peculiar\Nthings like that exist in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.02,0:20:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of the sky island, one of my\Nexplorer friends showed me a live skyfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.59,0:20:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was surprised at how strange the fish looked.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.92,0:20:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Skyfish?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.26,0:20:38.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To our ship, it's still an unknown area,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.26,0:20:42.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but as a sailor, I'd like to go\Nto the sea in the sky one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.27,0:20:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Montblanc Noland...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.60,0:20:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said "the sea in the sky"!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.27,0:20:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like Robin said!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.27,0:20:52.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it sounds like the sky island was a\Npretty normal thing for people back them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.28,0:20:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it really does exist!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.94,0:20:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.28,0:20:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, old-timer! How are you feeling?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.98,0:21:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't be better!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.25,0:21:03.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Glad to hear it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.25,0:21:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old-timer, this bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.92,0:21:08.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up and listen. Do you like those guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.26,0:21:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.26,0:21:14.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like they wanna go\Nto the sky island at any cost.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.26,0:21:19.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sky island... If they wanna go,\Nthere's only one way to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.27,0:21:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they try on their own, they'll get\Nkilled immediately, old-timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.61,0:21:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly... so why don't we give them a hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.20,0:22:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, beyond the never-ending sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.31,0:22:12.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The future that I once saw\Nis now starting to take shape
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.66,0:22:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are days where I almost lose to myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.17,0:22:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When that happened, there was\Nsomeplace warm I could go
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.55,0:22:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The friends I took pride in\Nalways, without fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.69,0:22:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pushed me onwards, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.70,0:23:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the stars are pouring\Ndown underneath the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.97,0:23:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This unique moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.35,0:23:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can finally go to the sky! To the sky!!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.02,0:23:15.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what kind of place the sky island is!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.39,0:23:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.72,0:23:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an adventure befitting me, Captain Usopp!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.72,0:23:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it'll be a life-threatening voyage.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.73,0:23:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it'll be a life-threatening...\NWhat? Hey, Luffy, let's forget about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.73,0:23:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.40,0:23:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.07,0:23:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Steer for the Clouds! Capture the South Bird!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.07,0:23:33.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.40,0:23:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
